parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft actuator bolts can cause the engine to stop working, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The flawed design of the coolant pipe can cause massive coolant leaks, leading to engine overheating and potentially causing accidents or engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the transfer case can cause sudden jerking, loss of acceleration, and grinding sensations while driving, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Sudden jerking or hesitation when accelerating
grinding or clunking noises while driving
surging or hesitation when shifting gears
feeling of the front wheel locking up
sudden lurching forward when coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coolant System Failure due to Faulty Plastic Tubing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty plastic tubing can cause coolant leaks, leading to overheating and engine damage, which can result in costly repairs and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Coolant leaks while the vehicle is stationary

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hybrid system failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and functionality, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: failure to recharge the hybrid system
intermittent error messages that may disappear and reappear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transfer case failure can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents. Over time, it can also cause wear on the front and rear differentials of an AWD vehicle.
symptoms: wear on front and rear differentials.
